Privacy Policy

Application Name: Sword and Shield

Personal Information Collected: We collect the following types of personal information from users:

Name: We collect your name to personalize the user experience, allow players to identify one another during multiplayer gameplay, and enable leaderboards and social features that enhance user interaction.
Email Address: Your email address is collected for purposes such as account creation, password recovery, game updates, and important notifications related to security or functionality. It is also used for communication regarding service enhancements or promotions, but only with your consent.
Gameplay Data: This includes data such as level progression, game statistics, items collected, achievements, in-game preferences, and leaderboard standings. This data helps us enhance your gaming experience by providing tailored content, ensuring continuity of play, and offering suitable challenges.
User Location: Location information is collected to optimize the performance of multiplayer services, such as connecting players from similar regions to minimize latency issues. Additionally, it may be used to tailor game events or content that is region-specific to provide a more engaging experience.
Purpose of Information Collection: We collect personal information for the following purposes:

Enhance User Experience: The information collected allows us to understand user behavior and preferences, helping us to develop personalized features and content that enhance user engagement. For example, gameplay data allows us to adjust the difficulty level or make personalized in-game suggestions.
Provide Multiplayer Services: By using personal information like location data and in-game preferences, we can provide a smoother and more enjoyable multiplayer experience, reduce latency, and optimize server usage for better game quality.
Customer Support: Collected information is used to assist players in resolving issues they may encounter while using our game. This includes technical troubleshooting and responding to support requests.
Security and Fraud Prevention: Information is used to monitor user accounts for suspicious activities in order to prevent unauthorized access or fraudulent behaviors, ensuring that the game remains fair for all players.
Improve Game Quality: The collected data is analyzed to identify bugs, enhance game performance, and develop new features that cater to user interests. Feedback collected via gameplay patterns helps us iterate and improve our services continuously.
Information Sharing with Third Parties: We do not share any collected personal information with third parties. All user data remains confidential and is used solely by Sword and Shield for improving and providing game services.

Data Retention and Protection Policy:

Data Retention: We retain user data as long as an account remains active. Upon deletion of an account, all associated data, including personal information, gameplay data, and progress, will be permanently deleted from our servers. Backup copies may persist for a limited period as part of our regular backup process but will be removed thereafter.
Data Security: We employ industry-standard security measures to safeguard all data collected from users. This includes encryption during data transmission, secure storage environments, access control, and routine audits to detect vulnerabilities and ensure data integrity. Only authorized personnel are allowed to access sensitive data, and stringent measures are in place to prevent unauthorized access.
Children's Privacy: Our services are intended for individuals aged 13 and older. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. If we become aware that such data has been inadvertently collected, we will take steps to delete it promptly. If a parent or guardian becomes aware that their child has provided us with information without consent, they should contact us to have the information removed.

User Rights:

Access and Correction: Users may access, correct, or update their personal information through the account settings page in the game. Any requests for correction of inaccuracies will be addressed promptly.
Data Deletion: Users have the right to request the deletion of their account and all associated data by contacting our support team. Upon receiving such requests, we will delete all user information as required by applicable laws.
Data Portability: Upon request, users can obtain a copy of their personal data in a portable format, allowing them to transfer data to another service if desired.
Contact Information: If you have any questions or concerns regarding our Privacy Policy or your data, feel free to reach out to us through the following channels:

Fanpage: https://www.facebook.com/minhlostudio/
Group: https://www.facebook.com/groups/minhlostudogroups
